column22: select cast(($1 + $2) as timestamp with time zone)
select description from pg_catalog.pg_description where objoid = $1 and classoid = (select oid from pg_catalog.pg_class where relname = $2 and relnamespace = 11) and objsubid = 0
select description from pg_catalog.pg_description where objoid = $1 and classoid = 'pg_catalog.pg_class'::pg_catalog.regclass and objsubid = $2
select description from pg_catalog.pg_shdescription where objoid = $1 and classoid = (select oid from pg_catalog.pg_class where relname = $2 and relnamespace = 11)
select description from pg_catalog.pg_description where objoid = $1 and objsubid = 0
select cast(cast($1 as timestamp without time zone) as pg_catalog.time)
select pg_catalog.date_part($1, cast($2 as timestamp with time zone))
select pg_catalog.date_part($1, cast($2 as timestamp without time zone))
select pg_catalog.age(cast(current_date as timestamp with time zone), $1)
select pg_catalog.age(cast(current_date as timestamp without time zone), $1)
SELECT CASE WHEN $2.typtype = 'd' THEN $2.typbasetype ELSE $1.atttypid END

SELECT 
    tt.alias AS alias,
    tt.description AS description,
    parse.token AS token,
    ARRAY ( SELECT m.mapdict::pg_catalog.regdictionary
            FROM pg_catalog.pg_ts_config_map AS m
            WHERE m.mapcfg = $1 AND m.maptokentype = parse.tokid
            ORDER BY m.mapseqno )
    AS dictionaries,
    ( SELECT mapdict::pg_catalog.regdictionary
      FROM pg_catalog.pg_ts_config_map AS m
      WHERE m.mapcfg = $1 AND m.maptokentype = parse.tokid
      ORDER BY pg_catalog.ts_lexize(mapdict, parse.token) IS NULL, m.mapseqno
      LIMIT 1
    ) AS dictionary,
    ( SELECT pg_catalog.ts_lexize(mapdict, parse.token)
      FROM pg_catalog.pg_ts_config_map AS m
      WHERE m.mapcfg = $1 AND m.maptokentype = parse.tokid
      ORDER BY pg_catalog.ts_lexize(mapdict, parse.token) IS NULL, m.mapseqno
      LIMIT 1
    ) AS lexemes
FROM pg_catalog.ts_parse(
        (SELECT cfgparser FROM pg_catalog.pg_ts_config WHERE oid = $1 ), $2 
    ) AS parse,
     pg_catalog.ts_token_type(
        (SELECT cfgparser FROM pg_catalog.pg_ts_config WHERE oid = $1 )
    ) AS tt
WHERE tt.tokid = parse.tokid

select $1[s], s - pg_catalog.array_lower($1,1) + 1
        from pg_catalog.generate_series(pg_catalog.array_lower($1,1),
                                        pg_catalog.array_upper($1,1),
                                        1) as g(s)

SELECT refobjid FROM pg_catalog.pg_depend
  WHERE classid = 'pg_catalog.pg_constraint'::pg_catalog.regclass AND
        objid = $1 AND
        refclassid = 'pg_catalog.pg_class'::pg_catalog.regclass AND
        refobjsubid = 0 AND deptype = 'n'

SELECT (ss.a).n FROM
  (SELECT information_schema._pg_expandarray(indkey) AS a
   FROM pg_catalog.pg_index WHERE indexrelid = $1) ss
  WHERE (ss.a).x = $2;
SELECT CASE WHEN $2.typtype = 'd' THEN $2.typtypmod ELSE $1.atttypmod END

SELECT
  CASE WHEN $2 = -1 /* default typmod */
       THEN null
       WHEN $1 IN (1042, 1043) /* char, varchar */
       THEN $2 - 4
       WHEN $1 IN (1560, 1562) /* bit, varbit */
       THEN $2
       ELSE null
  END

SELECT
  CASE WHEN $1 IN (25, 1042, 1043) /* text, char, varchar */
       THEN CAST(2^30 AS integer)
       ELSE null
  END

SELECT
  CASE $1
         WHEN 21 /*int2*/ THEN 16
         WHEN 23 /*int4*/ THEN 32
         WHEN 20 /*int8*/ THEN 64
         WHEN 1700 /*numeric*/ THEN
              CASE WHEN $2 = -1
                   THEN null
                   ELSE (($2 - 4) >> 16) & 65535
                   END
         WHEN 700 /*float4*/ THEN 24 /*FLT_MANT_DIG*/
         WHEN 701 /*float8*/ THEN 53 /*DBL_MANT_DIG*/
         ELSE null
  END

SELECT
  CASE WHEN $1 IN (21, 23, 20, 700, 701) THEN 2
       WHEN $1 IN (1700) THEN 10
       ELSE null
  END

SELECT
  CASE WHEN $1 IN (21, 23, 20) THEN 0
       WHEN $1 IN (1700) THEN
            CASE WHEN $2 = -1
                 THEN null
                 ELSE ($2 - 4) & 65535
                 END
       ELSE null
  END

SELECT
  CASE WHEN $1 IN (1082) /* date */
           THEN 0
       WHEN $1 IN (1083, 1114, 1184, 1266) /* time, timestamp, same + tz */
           THEN CASE WHEN $2 < 0 THEN 6 ELSE $2 END
       WHEN $1 IN (1186) /* interval */
           THEN CASE WHEN $2 < 0 THEN 6 ELSE $2 & 65535 END
       ELSE null
  END
